This is a starter patch for the OpenThread copy used by ESP-IDF. It is written
as an implementation guide rather than a guaranteed `git apply` patch because
ESP-IDF vendors specific OpenThread revisions.

Target idea:
  * Add public C APIs:
      otThreadSearchForPreferredParentRloc16(instance, rloc16)
      otThreadSearchForPreferredParentExtAddress(instance, extaddr)
      otThreadSetPreferredParentRloc16(instance, rloc16)
      otThreadSetPreferredParentExtAddress(instance, extaddr)
      otThreadClearPreferredParent(instance)
  * Add an MLE attach mode that accepts only Parent Responses whose candidate
    parent identifier matches the requested RLOC16 or IEEE 802.15.4 Extended
    Address.
  * When this preferred mode is active, bypass the normal "better parent"
    comparison. This is intentional: the user is explicitly forcing the parent.

--- include/openthread/thread.h
+++ include/openthread/thread.h
@@
 otError otThreadSearchForBetterParent(otInstance *aInstance);
+
+/**
+ * Starts a parent search that only accepts a Parent Response from `aParentRloc16`.
+ *
+ * This is a non-standard extension intended for controlled diagnostics and
+ * experiments, not general Thread behavior.
+ */
+otError otThreadSearchForPreferredParentRloc16(otInstance *aInstance, uint16_t aParentRloc16);
+
+/**
+ * Starts a parent search that only accepts a Parent Response from `aParentExtAddress`.
+ *
+ * This is a non-standard extension intended for controlled diagnostics and
+ * experiments, not general Thread behavior.
+ */
+otError otThreadSearchForPreferredParentExtAddress(otInstance *aInstance, const otExtAddress *aParentExtAddress);
+
+/** Sets the preferred parent RLOC16 used by the preferred-parent attach mode. */
+otError otThreadSetPreferredParentRloc16(otInstance *aInstance, uint16_t aParentRloc16);
+
+/** Sets the preferred parent extended address used by the preferred-parent attach mode. */
+otError otThreadSetPreferredParentExtAddress(otInstance *aInstance, const otExtAddress *aParentExtAddress);
+
+/** Clears any preferred parent target. */
+void otThreadClearPreferredParent(otInstance *aInstance);
 
